{{Context|date=October 2009}}
A belief in the '''primacy of mind''' is {{cns|an ubiquitous element in the [[history of ideas]]|date=November 2018}}. In this view the [[mind]] or [[soul]] is not only [[Idealism|primary as an explanation of reality]], but is the only conceivable explanation, as nothing so subtle and sublime as reason and morality could possibly [[Materialism|emerge from matter and motion]], the primary elements of scientific explanation.{{cn|date=November 2018}} In his book ''[[Darwin's Dangerous Idea]]'', [[Daniel Dennett]] states that a central aspect of Judeo-Christian and Islamic [[cosmogony]] is that, in the beginning, there was "something with Mind—'a cogitative Being,'".<ref>Dennett, D. C., ''[[Darwin's Dangerous Idea: Evolution and the Meanings of Life]]'', 1995, p26, {{ISBN|0-684-82471-X}}</ref>
